\f0\b Sorting\

\f1\b0 A switch on the browser window controls whether or not rows are automatically sorted as columns are rearranged.  This demonstrates the very powerful built-in sorting capability of MiscTableScroll.  Sorting can be fine-tuned right in the 
\f2\i nib
\f1\i0  file by adjusting the criteria on a column-by-column basis.  For instance, columns may contribute 
\f2\i stringValue, title, intValue, tag, 
\f1\i0 etc. to the row-wise comparisons.\
