\f0\b \cf0 Image Display\

\f1\b0 One column in the browser displays the file's icon.  This demonstrates how to use 
\f2\i image
\f1\i0  columns in addition to 
\f2\i text
\f1\i0  columns.\
\

\f0\b Image Dragging\

\f1\b0 MiscTableScroll allows images to be dragged directly out cells.  In this example, the file's icon can be dragged directly from the directory browser into any other application which accepts 
\f2\i dragged filenames
\f1\i0 , such as File Viewer, Mail, Edit, etc.  A button controls whether or not the scaled or full-size image is used during the dragging operation.  This illustrates how the delegate can optionally substitute an image in place of the one already contained in the cell.\
\
