\f0\b \cf0 Buttons\
\pard\tx960\tx1920\tx2880\tx3840\tx4800\tx5760\tx6720\tx7680\tx8640\tx9600\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 This example illustrates how to use 
\f2\i ButtonCells
\f1\i0  with the MiscTableScroll.  One column contains a 
\f2\i ButtonCell
\f1\i0  configured as a toggle switch.  It displays a padlock in either a locked or unlocked state and clicking on it toggles its state.  The padlock indicates whether or not the file can be renamed.  When 
\f2\i unlocked,
\f1\i0  renaming is allowed, and double-clicking on the file name in the 
\f2\i Name
\f1\i0  column initiates an edit session.  When 
\f2\i locked,
\f1\i0  renaming is not allowed.  If you do not have permission to rename a file the browser displays a 
\f2\i locked
\f1\i0  icon and disables the 
\f2\i ButtonCell
\f1\i0 .\
\
